@startuml
' Simplified architecture diagram for AI-assisted Knowledge Bank system

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
left to right direction

title Glencore Knowledge Bank - Simplified Architecture

actor "Employee / Expert Reviewer" as User

node "Frontend (React + Vite)" as FE {
  component "Web App UI" as FE_UI
}

node "Backend API (FastAPI)" as BE {
  component "Auth API" as B_Auth
  component "Document Workflow API\n(upload, review, apply)" as B_Workflow
  component "Knowledge Chat API\n(vector + fallback)" as B_Chat
}

cloud "Ollama Runtime\nlocalhost:11434" as OLLAMA

database "Workflow DB (SQLite)\ndatabases/workflow/workflow.sqlite3" as DB_SQL
folder "Uploads Storage\ndatabases/data/uploads" as FS_Uploads
folder "Knowledge Base Raw\ndatabases/knowledge_base/raw" as FS_KB
storage "Vector Store (Chroma)\ndatabases/vector_store/chroma" as DB_Vector

User --> FE_UI : Use system

FE_UI --> B_Auth : Login / refresh token
FE_UI --> B_Workflow : Upload, review, apply
FE_UI --> B_Chat : Ask questions

B_Auth --> DB_SQL : users + sessions

B_Workflow --> FS_Uploads : store uploaded files
B_Workflow --> DB_SQL : suggestions/reviews/audit
B_Workflow --> FS_KB : write approved docs
B_Workflow --> DB_Vector : reindex approved docs
B_Workflow --> OLLAMA : embeddings during indexing

B_Chat --> DB_Vector : vector retrieval
B_Chat --> FS_KB : lexical fallback
B_Chat --> OLLAMA : final answer generation

note right of B_Chat
Knowledge chat retrieval:
1) Vector-first (Chroma)
2) Lexical fallback (KB files)
end note

note bottom of B_Workflow
Apply flow triggers background reindex
and updates reindex status for UI.
end note

@enduml
